HEADWORD: Monolith
<hw>Mon"o*lith</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>monolithe</ets>, L. <ets>monolithus</ets> consisting of a single
stone, Gr. <?/; <grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <grk>li`qos</grk>
stone.]</ety> <def>A single stone, especially one of large size, shaped
into a pillar, statue, or monument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monolithal</ent>⟦br⟧
